desc: HUNTAIL’s presence went unnoticed by people for a long time because it lives at extreme depths in the sea. This POKéMON’s eyes can see clearly even in the murky dark depths of the ocean.

name: gorebyss
desc: GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this POKéMON’s body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.

name: relicanth
desc: RELICANTH is a POKéMON species that existed for a hundred million years without ever changing its form. This ancient POKéMON feeds on microscopic organisms with its toothless mouth.

name: luvdisc
desc: LUVDISC live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped POKéMON earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean’s waves.

name: bagon
desc: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

name: shelgon
desc: Inside SHELGON’s armor-like shell, cells are in the midst of transformation to create an entirely new body. This POKéMON’s shell is extremely heavy, making its movements sluggish.

name: salamence
desc: By evolving into Salamence, this Pokémon finally realizes its long-held dream of growing wings. To express its joy, it flies and wheels all over the sky while spouting flames from its mouth.

name: salamence
desc: SALAMENCE came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this POKéMON’s cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.

name: beldum
desc: Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout BELDUM’s body. This POKéMON communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.

name: metang
desc: When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG is formed. The brains of the BELDUM are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this POKéMON generates strong psychokinetic power.

name: metagross
desc: METAGROSS has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This POKéMON can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.

name: metagross
desc: Metagross is the result of two Metang achieving fusion. When hunting, this Pokémon pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large mouth on its stomach.

name: regirock
desc: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.

name: regice
desc: REGICE’s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can’t be melted, even by fire. This POKéMON controls frigid air of minus 328 degrees F.

name: registeel
desc: REGISTEEL has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this POKéMON eats.

name: latias
desc: LATIAS is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this POKéMON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe. It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible. Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

name: latias
desc: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe. Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

name: latios
desc: LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKéMON is intelligent and understands human speech.  It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

name: latios
desc: LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKéMON is intelligent and understands human speech. Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

name: kyogre
desc: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.

name: kyogre
desc: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.  Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

name: groudon
desc: GROUDON has long been described in mythology as the POKéMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKéMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.

name: groudon
desc: GROUDON has long been described in mythology as the POKéMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKéMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.  Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

name: rayquaza
desc: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer, never descending to the ground. This POKéMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere.

name: rayquaza
desc: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer, never descending to the ground. This POKéMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere. It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

name: jirachi
desc: A legend states that JIRACHI will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this POKéMON senses danger, it will fight without awakening.

name: deoxys
desc: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest. The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS.

name: deoxys
desc: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen. The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS.

name: deoxys
desc: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS. The crystalline organ on this POKéMON’s chest appears to be its brain. An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteorite underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: deoxys
desc: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon's chest appears to be its brain. The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS.

name: turtwig
desc: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

name: grotle
desc: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

name: torterra
desc: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

name: chimchar
desc: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

name: monferno
desc: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

name: infernape
desc: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

name: piplup
desc: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: prinplup
desc: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

name: empoleon
desc: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

name: starly
desc: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

name: staravia
desc: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

name: staraptor
desc: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.

name: bidoof
desc: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: bibarel
desc: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

name: kricketot
desc: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.

name: kricketune
desc: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

name: shinx
desc: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: luxio
desc: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

name: luxray
desc: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

name: budew
desc: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

name: roserade
desc: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.

name: cranidos
desc: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.

name: rampardos
desc: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

name: shieldon
desc: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.

name: bastiodon
desc: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

name: burmy
desc: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: wormadam
desc: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body. When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

name: wormadam
desc: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed. Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: wormadam
desc: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed. Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body. When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: mothim
desc: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.

name: combee
desc: A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.

name: vespiquen
desc: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.

name: pachirisu
desc: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: buizel
desc: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

name: floatzel
desc: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: cherubi
desc: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.

name: cherrim
desc: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.

name: shellos
desc: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

name: gastrodon
desc: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

name: ambipom
desc: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: drifloon
desc: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

name: drifblim
desc: At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.

name: buneary
desc: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

name: lopunny
desc: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

name: lopunny
desc: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs. Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.

name: mismagius
desc: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

name: honchkrow
desc: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.

name: glameow
desc: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: purugly
desc: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.

name: chingling
desc: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

name: stunky
desc: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

name: skuntank
desc: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

name: bronzor
desc: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

name: bronzong
desc: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

name: bonsly
desc: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body’s fluid levels by eliminating excess.

name: mime-jr
desc: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

name: happiny
desc: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.

name: chatot
desc: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: spiritomb
desc: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

name: gible
desc: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

name: gabite
desc: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

name: garchomp
desc: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

name: garchomp
desc: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed. It flies at speeds equals to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

name: munchlax
desc: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing. When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

name: riolu
desc: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

name: lucario
desc: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

name: lucario
desc: It understands human speech. By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements. By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

name: hippopotas
desc: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.

name: hippowdon
desc: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

name: skorupi
desc: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

name: drapion
desc: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

name: croagunk
desc: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

name: toxicroak
desc: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

name: carnivine
desc: It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: finneon
desc: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: lumineon
desc: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

name: mantyke
desc: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

name: snover
desc: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

name: abomasnow
desc: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.  It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as "The Ice Monster."

name: abomasnow
desc: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

name: weavile
desc: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: magnezone
desc: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

name: lickilicky
desc: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

name: rhyperior
desc: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.

name: tangrowth
desc: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

name: electivire
desc: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.

name: magmortar
desc: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

name: togekiss
desc: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

name: yanmega
desc: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

name: leafeon
desc: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

name: glaceon
desc: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

name: gliscor
desc: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: mamoswine
desc: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

name: porygon-z
desc: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

name: gallade
desc: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows. Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.

name: gallade
desc: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows. Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.

name: probopass
desc: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

name: dusknoir
desc: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

name: froslass
desc: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

name: rotom
desc: If the convection microwave oven is not working properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will become lethargic. This Rotom has possessed a convection microwave oven. It will sear the surrounding area with its burning heat, then smile in delight.

name: rotom
desc: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc. Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief. Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

name: rotom
desc: The lawn mower is one of the household appliances that led to the development of the Rotom Dex. This Rotom has possessed a lawn mower. It will mow down grass and flowers, then swagger around with pride at its accomplishments.

name: rotom
desc: This Rotom has entered a refrigerator. It leaps around gleefully after it uses cold air to freeze the area around it. The special motor within the refrigerator is the key to bringing about Rotom's change in form.

name: rotom
desc: This Rotom has entered a washing machine. It nods with satisfaction after it floods the surrounding area. The model of washing machine that Rotom can inspirit has been discontinued, so these appliances are now traded at high prices.

name: rotom
desc: This Rotom has entered an electric fan. It smirks with satisfaction over a prank well pulled after it blows away everything around it. There are several appliances that Rotom can inspirit, but the first one to be developed was the electric fan.

name: uxie
desc: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: mesprit
desc: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: azelf
desc: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: dialga
desc: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity. This Pokémon is spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born. This Pokémon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.

name: dialga
desc: Radiant light caused Dialga to take on a form bearing a striking resemblance to the creator Pokémon. Dialga now wields such colossal strength that one must conclude this is its true form.

name: palkia
desc: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology. It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. Palkia appears in mythology. This Pokémon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.

name: palkia
desc: It soars across the sky in a form that greatly resembles the creator of all things. Perhaps this imitation of appearance is Palkia’s strategy for gaining Arceus’s powers.

name: heatran
desc: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: regigigas
desc: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: giratina
desc: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery. There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.

name: giratina
desc: Giratina loses its legs upon changing into this form. I believe this Pokémon must hail from a world where the heavens and the earth are as one, though I have no way of proving it.

name: cresselia
desc: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: phione
desc: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

name: manaphy
desc: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

name: darkrai
desc: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: shaymin
desc: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant. It lives in common flower patches but is rarely noticed. It is often mistaken for a flowering plant when curled up. It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers. When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.

name: shaymin
desc: Upon taking in the scent of a particular rare flower, Shaymin is enveloped in light, and its tiny body transforms. I took a whiff of the flower myself, but alas, my body remained unchanged. It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: arceus
desc: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

name: victini
desc: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: snivy
desc: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

name: servine
desc: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: serperior
desc: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

name: tepig
desc: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: pignite
desc: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: emboar
desc: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: oshawott
desc: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: dewott
desc: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: samurott
desc: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokémon’s evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.

name: samurott
desc: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

name: patrat
desc: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

name: watchog
desc: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: lillipup
desc: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

name: herdier
desc: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: stoutland
desc: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: purrloin
desc: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

name: liepard
desc: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

name: pansage
desc: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

name: simisage
desc: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: pansear
desc: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

name: simisear
desc: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

name: panpour
desc: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: simipour
desc: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: munna
desc: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

name: musharna
desc: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

name: pidove
desc: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

name: tranquill
desc: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

name: unfezant
desc: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

name: blitzle
desc: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: zebstrika
desc: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: roggenrola
desc: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

name: boldore
desc: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

name: gigalith
desc: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

name: woobat
desc: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

name: swoobat
desc: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

name: drilbur
desc: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

name: excadrill
desc: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

name: audino
desc: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: audino
desc: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

name: timburr
desc: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

name: gurdurr
desc: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: conkeldurr
desc: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

name: tympole
desc: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

name: palpitoad
desc: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

name: seismitoad
desc: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

name: throh
desc: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

name: sawk
desc: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

name: sewaddle
desc: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: swadloon
desc: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: leavanny
desc: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: venipede
desc: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

name: whirlipede
desc: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

name: scolipede
desc: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

name: cottonee
desc: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

name: whimsicott
desc: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: petilil
desc: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

name: lilligant
desc: Essential oils made from Lilligant flowers have a sublime scent, but they're also staggeringly expensive. I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity. Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.

name: lilligant
desc: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities. It's believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant's head to bloom.

name: basculin
desc: Blue-striped Basculin used to be a common food source. They apparently have an inoffensive, light flavor. Known for their violence, these Pokémon have the most fights with schools of red- striped Basculin.

name: basculin
desc: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile. Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch— many people release them into lakes illicitly. In the past, it often appeared on the dinner table. The meat of red-striped Basculin is on the fatty side, and it's more popular with the youth.

name: basculin
desc: They live in frigid seas, forming schools and sharing food among themselves. When the time comes, they return to the river they were born in. Its ecology is starkly different from that of other Basculin, so theories that it's a totally different species have gained traction in recent years.

name: sandile
desc: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

name: krokorok
desc: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

name: krookodile
desc: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

name: darumaka
desc: It lived in snowy areas for so long that its fire sac cooled off and atrophied. It now has an organ that generates cold instead. The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.

name: darumaka
desc: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

name: darmanitan
desc: Anger has reignited its atrophied flame sac. This Pokémon spews fire everywhere as it rampages indiscriminately. Darmanitan takes this form when enraged. It won't stop spewing flames until its rage has settled, even if its body starts to melt.

name: darmanitan
desc: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch. The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck. This Pokémon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: darmanitan
desc: On days when blizzards blow through, it comes down to where people live. It stashes food in the snowball on its head, taking it home for later. Though it has a gentle disposition, it's also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.

name: darmanitan
desc: Through meditation, it calms its raging spirit and hones its psychic powers. When wounded, it stops moving. It goes as still as stone to meditate, sharpening its mind and spirit.

name: maractus
desc: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

name: dwebble
desc: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

name: crustle
desc: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: scraggy
desc: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: scrafty
desc: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

name: sigilyph
desc: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

name: yamask
desc: A clay slab with cursed engravings took possession of a Yamask. The slab is said to be absorbing the Yamask's dark power.It's said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.

name: yamask
desc: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry. It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that's said to have been the face it had when it was still human. The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.

name: cofagrigus
desc: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

name: tirtouga
desc: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: carracosta
desc: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: archen
desc: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: archeops
desc: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: trubbish
desc: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: garbodor
desc: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: garbodor
desc: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: zorua
desc: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child. Zorua is a timid Pokémon. This disposition seems to be what led to the development of Zorua's ability to take on the forms of other creatures.

name: zorua
desc: Zorua sometimes transforms into a person and goes into cities to search for food. When Zorua does this, it usually takes on the form of a child. A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.

name: zoroark
desc: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: zoroark
desc: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark’s own body. Seeking to ease the burden of their solitude, lonely Trainers tell Zoroark to show illusions to them. This Pokémon cares deeply about others of its kind, and it will conjure terrifying illusions to keep its den and pack safe.

name: minccino
desc: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

name: cinccino
desc: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

name: gothita
desc: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: gothorita
desc: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: gothitelle
desc: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: solosis
desc: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: duosion
desc: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: reuniclus
desc: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: ducklett
desc: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

name: swanna
desc: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: vanillite
desc: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

name: vanillish
desc: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

name: vanilluxe
desc: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

name: deerling
desc: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

name: sawsbuck
desc: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

name: emolga
desc: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

name: karrablast
desc: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

name: escavalier
desc: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

name: foongus
desc: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

name: amoonguss
desc: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

name: frillish
desc: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: jellicent
desc: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: alomomola
desc: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

name: joltik
desc: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

name: galvantula
desc: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: ferroseed
desc: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: ferrothorn
desc: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: klink
desc: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

name: klang
desc: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

name: klinklang
desc: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: tynamo
desc: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: eelektrik
desc: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: eelektross
desc: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: elgyem
desc: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: beheeyem
desc: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

name: litwick
desc: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

name: lampent
desc: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: chandelure
desc: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: axew
desc: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

name: fraxure
desc: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

name: haxorus
desc: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

name: cubchoo
desc: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

name: beartic
desc: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: cryogonal
desc: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

name: shelmet
desc: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

name: accelgor
desc: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

name: stunfisk
desc: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity. Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokémon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity. For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

name: stunfisk
desc: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body. Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.

name: mienfoo
desc: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: mienshao
desc: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

name: druddigon
desc: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

name: golett
desc: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

name: golurk
desc: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

name: pawniard
desc: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

name: bisharp
desc: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

name: bouffalant
desc: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

name: rufflet
desc: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: braviary
desc: Because this Pokémon is hotheaded and belligerent, it's Corviknight that's taken the role of transportation in Galar. Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokémon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water’s surface.

name: braviary
desc: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying. Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokémon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.

name: vullaby
desc: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

name: mandibuzz
desc: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

name: heatmor
desc: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

name: durant
desc: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

name: deino
desc: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

name: zweilous
desc: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

name: hydreigon
desc: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

name: larvesta
desc: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

name: volcarona
desc: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

name: cobalion
desc: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

name: terrakion
desc: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

name: virizion
desc: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

name: tornadus
desc: An example of what is known as a “form change,” though I suspect this strange avian guise to be Tornadus’s true form. Tornadus has been sighted crossing the ocean while in this form.

name: tornadus
desc: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph. This storm-stirring Pokémon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.

name: thundurus
desc: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed. They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.

name: thundurus
desc: Quick as a flash, it materializes out of nowhere. It pulverizes foes into nothingness with showers of devastatingly powerful lightning bolts launched from the string of orbs on its tail.

name: reshiram
desc: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it. Flames spew from its tail as it flies through the sky like a jet airplane. It's said that this Pokémon will scorch the world. According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

name: zekrom
desc: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail. When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings. Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom's lightning.

name: landorus
desc: Landorus soars through the sky in this form, bestowing plentiful harvests upon the land and earning the people’s reverence. It can traverse the whole of Hisui in a mere couple of hours.

name: landorus
desc: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.” When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.

name: kyurem
desc: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out. Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound. It appears that this Pokémon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.

name: kyurem
desc: It's said that this Pokémon battles in order to protect the ideal world that will exist in the future for people and Pokémon. The sameness of Zekrom's and Kyurem's genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Zekrom. Kyurem can now use the power of both electricity and ice.

name: kyurem
desc: The sameness of Reshiram's and Kyurem's genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Reshiram. Kyurem can now use the power of both fire and ice. It has foreseen that a world of truth will arrive for people and Pokémon. It strives to protect that future.

name: keldeo
desc: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling. Cobalion, Terrakion, and Virizion taught this Pokémon how to fight. It dashes across the world, seeking more opportunities to further its training. They say that Keldeo must survive harsh battles and fully develop the horn on its forehead before this Pokémon's true power will awaken. Keldeo has strengthened its resolve for battle, filling its body with power and changing its form. The power that lay hidden in its body now covers its horn, turning it into a sword that can slice through anything.

name: meloetta
desc: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it. The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad. Many famous songs have been inspired by the melodies that Meloetta plays.

name: meloetta
desc: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it. The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad. The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

name: genesect
desc: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.

name: chespin
desc: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

name: quilladin
desc: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

name: chesnaught
desc: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

name: fennekin
desc: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: braixen
desc: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

name: delphox
desc: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

name: froakie
desc: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: frogadier
desc: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: greninja
desc: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two. It makes shuriken out of mucus excreted from its thighs. These shuriken can cut cleanly through steel cables.

name: greninja
desc: The movement of air against the long tongue Greninja keeps wrapped around its neck allows it to sense enemies it can't see.

name: bunnelby
desc: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

name: diggersby
desc: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

name: fletchling
desc: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

name: fletchinder
desc: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

name: talonflame
desc: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

name: scatterbug
desc: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

name: spewpa
desc: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

name: vivillon
desc: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

name: litleo
desc: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

name: pyroar
desc: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

name: flabebe
desc: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.

name: floette
desc: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

name: florges
desc: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

name: skiddo
desc: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

name: gogoat
desc: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

name: pancham
desc: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

name: pangoro
desc: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

name: furfrou
desc: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

name: espurr
desc: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

name: meowstic
desc: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

name: honedge
desc: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

name: doublade
desc: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

name: aegislash
desc: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

name: aegislash
desc: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

name: spritzee
desc: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

name: aromatisse
desc: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

name: swirlix
desc: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

name: slurpuff
desc: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

name: inkay
desc: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

name: malamar
desc: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

name: binacle
desc: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

name: barbaracle
desc: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

name: skrelp
desc: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

name: dragalge
desc: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

name: clauncher
desc: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

name: clawitzer
desc: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

name: helioptile
desc: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

name: heliolisk
desc: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

name: tyrunt
desc: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

name: tyrantrum
desc: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

name: amaura
desc: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

name: aurorus
desc: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

name: sylveon
desc: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

name: hawlucha
desc: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

name: dedenne
desc: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

name: carbink
desc: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.

name: goomy
desc: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.

name: sliggoo
desc: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui’s water. The swirly protrusion on its back is filled with all its vital organs, such as its brain and heart. When Sliggoo senses danger, the mucus coating its entire body becomes more concentrated- it'll dissolve anything.

name: sliggoo
desc: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything. Although this Pokémon isn't very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it. The lump on its back contains its tiny brain. It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies. When Sliggoo senses danger, the mucus coating its entire body becomes more concentrated- it'll dissolve anything.

name: goodra
desc: It loves the rain. This mellow Pokémon can be seen walking around on the plains and in the mountains on rainy days. This Pokémon is uncontrollable when enraged. It rampages on and on, lashing its tail with enough power to send a dump truck flying. Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy—it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.

name: goodra
desc: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime. Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don't mind, finding this behavior to be adorable. Its form of offense is forcefully stretching out its horns. The strikes land 100 times harder than any blow from a heavyweight boxer.

name: klefki
desc: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.

name: phantump
desc: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

name: trevenant
desc: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

name: pumpkaboo
desc: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

name: gourgeist
desc: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

name: bergmite
desc: It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

name: avalugg
desc: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

name: avalugg
desc: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokémon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow. As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokémon's body returns to a pristine state overnight. At high latitudes, this Pokémon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

name: noibat
desc: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

name: noivern
desc: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

name: xerneas
desc: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

name: yveltal
desc: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

name: zygarde
desc: Its sharp fangs make short work of finishing off its enemies, but it’s unable to maintain this body indefinitely. After a period of time, it falls apart.         This is Zygarde’s form when about 10% of its cells have been gathered. It runs across the land at speeds greater than 60mph. This is Zygarde when about 10% of its pieces have been assembled. It leaps at its opponent’s chest and sinks its sharp fangs into them. Born when around 10% of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered from all over, this form is skilled in close-range combat.

name: zygarde
desc: This is Zygarde’s form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.  This is Zygarde’s 100% form. It has enough power to overwhelm even Xerneas or Yveltal. This is Zygarde’s perfected form. From the orifice on its chest, it radiates high-powered energy that eliminates everything.  Born when all of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered together, it uses force to neutralize those who harm the ecosystem.

name: zygarde
desc: When the Kalos region’s ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power. This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy. It’s thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it. This is Zygarde’s form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem. Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

name: diancie
desc: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: diancie
desc: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: hoopa
desc: In its true form, it possess a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within. It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

name: hoopa
desc: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space. It gathers things it likes and pushes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

name: volcanion
desc: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

name: rowlet
desc: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

name: dartrix
desc: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

name: decidueye
desc: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss. In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent's weak point before they notice what's happening. The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye’s feathers insulates the Pokémon against Hisui’s extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.

name: decidueye
desc: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards. It nocks its arrow quills and looses them at opponents. When it needs to hit, it pulls the vines on its hood to narrow its view and focus.

name: litten
desc: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

name: torracat
desc: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

name: incineroar
desc: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it’s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer’s orders with complete nonchalance.

name: popplio
desc: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It’s famous for being a hard worker.

name: brionne
desc: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.

name: primarina
desc: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

name: pikipek
desc: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

name: trumbeak
desc: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

name: toucannon
desc: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

name: yungoos
desc: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

name: gumshoos
desc: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing by nightfall.

name: grubbin
desc: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

name: charjabug
desc: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.

name: vikavolt
desc: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

name: crabrawler
desc: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

name: crabominable
desc: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

name: oricorio
desc: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames. This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind. It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames. This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

name: oricorio
desc: This Oricorio has sipped bright yellow nectar. Its bright, cheerful dance melts the hearts of its enemies. It creates an electric charge by rubbing its feathers together. It dances over to its enemies and delivers shocking electrical punches. It lifts its opponents’ spirits with its cheerful dance moves. When they let their guard down, it electrocutes them with a jolt. This Oricorio has drunk bright yellow nectar. When it sees someone looking glum, it will try to cheer them up with a dance.

name: oricorio
desc: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Its elegant, attractive dance will send the minds and hearts of its enemies to another world. It summons the dead with its dreamy dancing. From their malice, it draws power with which to curse its enemies. It charms its opponents with its refined dancing. When they let their guard down, it places a curse on them that will bring on their demise. This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Some dancers use its graceful, elegant dancing as inspiration.

name: oricorio
desc: This Oricorio relaxes by swaying gently. This increases its psychic energy, which it then fires at its enemies. This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. Its enemies’ hearts melt at the sight of its gently swaying hips. It relaxes its opponents with its elegant dancing. When they let their guard down, it showers them with psychic energy. This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. It gets so caught up in its dancing that it sometimes doesn’t hear its Trainer’s orders.

name: cutiefly
desc: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it’s able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

name: ribombee
desc: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

name: rockruff
desc: It’s considered to be a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

name: lycanroc
desc: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons. This form of Lycanroc is normally calm and quiet. Once a battle begins, however, this Pokémon displays a ferocious fighting spirit. These Pokémon have both calm and ferocious qualities. Their temperamental nature makes them a difficult species to raise.

name: lycanroc
desc: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons. This form of Lycanroc is reckless. It charges headlong at its opponents, attacking without any care about what injuries it might receive. It's invigorated by powerful opponents—the stronger the better. A full-force headbutt from one of these Lycanroc can shatter giant boulders.

name: lycanroc
desc: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons. This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp. With swift movements, this Pokémon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc's fangs are always aimed toward opponents' weak spots.

name: wishiwashi
desc: On their own, they're very weak. But when Wishiwashi pool their power together in a school, they become a demon of the sea. When facing tough opponents, they get into formation. But if they get wounded in battle, they'll scatter and become solitary again.

name: wishiwashi
desc: When it’s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies. Individually, they're incredibly weak. It's by gathering up into schools that they're able to confront opponents.

name: mareanie
desc: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

name: toxapex
desc: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.

name: mudbray
desc: The mud stuck to Mudbray’s hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

name: mudsdale
desc: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

name: dewpider
desc: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

name: araquanid
desc: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.

name: fomantis
desc: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

name: lurantis
desc: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’s vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

name: morelull
desc: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

name: shiinotic
desc: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.

name: salandit
desc: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

name: salazzle
desc: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

name: stufful
desc: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

name: bewear
desc: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.

name: bounsweet
desc: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.

name: steenee
desc: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

name: tsareena
desc: Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

name: comfey
desc: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.

name: oranguru
desc: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it’s best suited to veteran Trainers.

name: passimian
desc: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.

name: wimpod
desc: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

name: golisopod
desc: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

name: sandygast
desc: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.

name: palossand
desc: Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.

name: pyukumuku
desc: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

name: type-null
desc: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.

name: silvally
desc: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

name: minior
desc: It eats dust in the atmosphere. The composition of the dust determines the color of its core. If its core stays exposed, it will soon die off. It’s possible that it may survive if it’s put into a Poké Ball quickly enough. Places where Minior fall from the night sky are few and far between, with Alola being one of the precious few. This is its form when its shell has fallen off. The color of its core depends on the materials that made up the food it ate.

name: minior
